SIMPLE: unrighteous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unrighteous
<hw>Un*right"eous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>unrightwise</ets>, AS. <ets>unrihtw⟦imac⟧s</ets>. See <er>Un-</er>
not, and <er>Righteous</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>Not righteous; evil; wicked; sinful; <as>as, an
<ex>unrighteous</ex> man</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Contrary to law and equity; unjust; <as>as, an
<ex>unrighteous</ex> decree or sentence</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p>-- <wordforms><wf>Un*right"eous*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos> --
<wf>Un*right"eous*ness</wf>, <pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unrightwise</ent>⟦br⟧
